<HEAD>World Series Tops Week; `Roseanne' Joins Top 10</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By KATHRYN BAKER</BYLINE>
<BYLINE>AP Television Writer</BYLINE>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 As baseball wrapped up its season, the new television season started taking place, as evidenced by a weekly Nielsens list that sported more entertainment shows and few reruns. The last three games of the five-game World Series joined `` The Cosby Show'' to give <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> the top four spots in the <ORGANIZATION> A.C. </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nielsen </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> rankings and a substantial victory last week. But everybody got a share of the top 10, with <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> adding its new sitcom `` Roseanne,'' the highest-rated premiere of an <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION> comedy since `` Joanie Loves Chachi'' 6 -LCB- years ago. <ORGANIZATION> CBS </ORGANIZATION> won the Sunday movie battle and got a top 10 rating from the conclusion of the two-part movie `` Jack the Ripper.'' The final game between the <ORGANIZATION> Los </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Angeles </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Dodgers </ORGANIZATION> and the <ORGANIZATION> Oakland </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> A </ORGANIZATION>'s was the week's highest-rated program with a 26.3 rating and 43 share. <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> won the week with an average prime-time rating of 18.8 to <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>'s 13.9 and CBS' 12.7. A rating point equals 904,000 homes with televisions. The share is a percentage of sets in use. The average rating for <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>'s coverage of the Series was 23.7, one point higher than the first five games of last year's series between <LOCATION> Minnesota </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Louis </LOCATION>. The top-rated shows of the week were: `` World Series _ Game 5,'' `` The Cosby Show,'' `` World Series _ Game 3'' and `` World Series _ Game 4,'' all on <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>; `` Roseanne'' and `` Who's the Boss?'' <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>; `` NBC Monday Night Movie _ Double Standard;'' `` 60 Minutes,'' `` CBS Sunday Movie _ Jack the Ripper, Part Two'' and `` Murder, She Wrote,'' CBS. <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>'s `` World News Tonight'' and the `` CBS Evening News'' tied for first place in the news category with an average 10.2 and 20 share. `` NBC Nightly News,'' pre-empted by baseball, had an 8.9 and 18. <ORGANIZATION> ABC </ORGANIZATION>'s limited-run remake of `` Mission Impossible'' made its debut at 24th. <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION>'s new `` Empty Nest'' was 16th. But `` Something Is Out There,'' based on last season's successful <ORGANIZATION> NBC </ORGANIZATION> miniseries, ranked only 42nd. The lowest-rated shows of the week were: `` Bugs Bunny: Battle of the Video Stars,'' `` Wiseguy special,'' `` 48 Hours,'' `` Incredible Sunday,'' `` <ORGANIZATION> Smothers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Brothers </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Special </ORGANIZATION>,'' `` MacGyver,'' `` West 57th,'' `` High Risk,'' `` Live! <PERSON> Dick </PERSON> <PERSON> Clark </PERSON> Present'' and `` <ORGANIZATION> Simon </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; <PERSON> Simon </PERSON>.''
