nd was lower than the charges for a similar cake at the supermarket that bears his family name. He is the former owner of a chain of supermarkets and department stores. In 1985, after he sold the stores, he spent $ 18.5 million to acquire the <ORGANIZATION> Milwaukee </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Bucks </ORGANIZATION> professional basketball team. <PERSON> Engeleiter </PERSON> contends <PERSON> Kohl </PERSON> should make more complete financial disclosure, but interviews and polls indicate the issue has had little effect on voters. `` There are basic issues beneath the surface, but the dynamics seem to be personal,'' said <ORGANIZATION> University </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Wisconsin </ORGANIZATION> history professor <PERSON> Margaret </PERSON> <PERSON> Bogue </PERSON>. State Historian <PERSON> William </PERSON> <PERSON> F. </PERSON> <PERSON> Thompson </PERSON> suggests that voters seem to be turned off this election, another departure from the past. `` <LOCATION> Wisconsin </LOCATION> traditionally has taken politics seriously, as opposed to cynically,'' <PERSON> Thompson </PERSON> said. <PERSON> Kohl </PERSON> led <PERSON> Engeleiter </PERSON> 57 percent to 34 percent among likely voters surveyed Oct. 6 and Oct. 7 by the <ORGANIZATION> Milwaukee </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Journal </ORGANIZATION>, but Republican strategists still contend <PERSON> Engeleiter </PERSON> could prevail. `` This is a very winnable race,'' said Sen. <PERSON> Alan </PERSON> <PERSON> Simpson </PERSON>, <LOCATION> R-Wyo </LOCATION>., who came to <LOCATION> Wisconsin </LOCATION> to campaign for <PERSON> Engeleiter </PERSON> last week Still, <PERSON> Kohl </PERSON>'s forces seem comfortable with their lead, and other Democrats are counting on <PERSON> Kohl </PERSON>'s coattails to help retain their majorities in the Legislature. <PERSON> Engeleiter </PERSON> tends to support the national Republican ticket and party platform on defense and budget issue