<HEAD>List Of Worst Marine Disasters</HEAD>
<HEAD>With AM-Ruby Bjt</HEAD>
<BYLINE>By The Associated Press</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
 Here is a list of major marine disasters in the 20th century: 1. Jan. 30, 1945: 6,000 Germans die in the icy <LOCATION> Baltic </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Sea </LOCATION> when the Nazi transport <PERSON> Wilhelm </PERSON> <PERSON> Gustloff </PERSON>, packed with Germans fleeing <LOCATION> Poland </LOCATION>, is torpedoed by a Soviet submarine. Only 903 people are saved. 2. November 1948: A <LOCATION> Chinese </LOCATION> merchant ship with as many as 6,000 people aboard explodes and sinks off southern <LOCATION> Manchuria </LOCATION>, killing all aboard, during the government evacuation of <LOCATION> Yingkow </LOCATION>. 3. Dec. 3, 1948: 3,920 die when the refugee ship Kiangya explodes and sinks near <LOCATION> Shanghai </LOCATION>. 4. Feb. 26, 1916: 3,100 killed when the French cruiser <LOCATION> Provence </LOCATION> sinks in the <LOCATION> Mediterranean </LOCATION>. 5. Dec. 20, 1987: MV <PERSON> Dona </PERSON> <PERSON> Paz </PERSON>, loaded with Christmas travelers, collides with the tanker MT <PERSON> Victor </PERSON> in the <LOCATION> Philippines </LOCATION>. At least 1,749 people are confirmed drowned but, because of overcrowding, the toll could have been more than 3,000. 6. Dec. 6, 1917: 1,600 killed when French ammunition ship <PERSON> Mont </PERSON> <PERSON> Blanc </PERSON> and Belgian steamer collide in <LOCATION> Halifax </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Harbor </LOCATION>. 7. April 14-15, 1912: 1,503 killed when British steamer Titanic hits iceberg in <LOCATION> North </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Atlantic </LOCATION>. 8. May 7, 1915: 1,198 killed when British steamer Lusitania sunk by German submarine off <LOCATION> Ireland </LOCATION>. 9. Sept. 26, 1954: 1,172 killed when Japanese ferry <ORGANIZATION> Toya </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Maru </ORGANIZATION> sinks in <LOCATION> Tsugaru </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Strait </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Japan </LOCATION>. 10. June 15, 1904: 1,030 killed when excursion steamer General <PERSON> Slocum </PERSON> burns in <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> <LOCATION> River </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> New </LOCATION> <LOCATION> York </LOCATION> <LOCATION> City </LOCATION>. 11. May 29, 1914: 1,014 killed when British steamer Empress of <LOCATION> Ireland </LOCATION> is sunk in collision with Norwegian collier in <LOCATION> St. </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Lawrence </LOCATION> <LOCATION> River </LOCATION>. 12. Aug. 29, 1916: 1,000 killed when Chinese steamer <PERSON> Hsin </PERSON> <PERSON> Yu </PERSON> sinks off Chinese coast. 13. March 18, 1921: 1,000 killed when steamer <LOCATION> Hong </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Kong </LOCATION> wrecks in <LOCATION> South </LOCATION> <LOCATION> China </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Sea </LOCATION>. 14. Sept. 28, 1912: 1,000 killed when Japanese steamer Kichemaru sinks off Japanese coast. 15. July 24, 1915: 812 killed when excursion steamer <LOCATION> Eastland </LOCATION> capsizes in <LOCATION> Chicago </LOCATION> <LOCATION> River </LOCATION>. 16. August 8, 1988: As many as 400 are drowned in <LOCATION> India </LOCATION> when an overcrowded ferry capsizes in the <LOCATION> Ganges </LOCATION> <LOCATION> River </LOCATION>.
