provide $ 6 million in rental assistance over the next five years. The tenants corporation plans to help tenants increase their incomes so they can afford to buy their apartments, said <PERSON> Alphonso </PERSON> <PERSON> Jackson </PERSON>, director of the city's <ORGANIZATION> Department </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> of </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Public </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Assisted </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Housing </ORGANIZATION>. So far, 132 residents have been removed from welfare rolls as result of the corporation's `` entrepreneurial ventures,'' such as a day care center and janitorial service, he said.
