LOCATION> was created in 1948. <PERSON> Yasser </PERSON> <PERSON> Arafat </PERSON>'s <ORGANIZATION> PLO </ORGANIZATION> has been studying possible plans for the future of Palestinians, including three choices: declaration of an independent Palestinian state in the Israeli-occupied territories, declaration of a provisional government or a combination of the two. <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> captured <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Bank </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Gaza </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Strip </LOCATION>, now home to about 1.5 million Palestinians, from <LOCATION> Jordan </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Egypt </LOCATION> in the 1967 <LOCATION> Middle </LOCATION> <LOCATION> East </LOCATION> war. <LOCATION> Egypt </LOCATION>, the only Arab nation ever to do so, signed a peace treaty with <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION> in 1979. <PERSON> Mubarak </PERSON> and <PERSON> Mitterrand </PERSON> last conferred in <LOCATION> Paris </LOCATION> on Sept. 27, during a European tour by the Egyptian president that included visits to <LOCATION> Britain </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> West </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Germany </LOCATION> and <LOCATION> Yugoslavia </LOCATION>.
