t the time she submitted the memo, Ms. <PERSON> Gabel </PERSON> conceded, she told her lawyer that she had not `` left out anything substantive.'' And Ms. <PERSON> Gabel </PERSON> admitted that in an interview with defense lawyers before the trial she said, `` There was no attempt by <PERSON> Miss </PERSON> <PERSON> Myerson </PERSON> to subvert governmental processes'' and agreed that <PERSON> Miss </PERSON> <PERSON> Myerson </PERSON> did not ask her to change her memory.
