Strip </LOCATION> on Dec. 8. Six Israelis also have died. Also Tuesday, an army spokesman confirmed that soldiers fatally shot a 17-year-old Palestinian during a clash Monday in the Faraa refugee camp near <LOCATION> Nablus </LOCATION>. The spokesman said troops fired rubber bullets after being attacked by youths throwing bottles and rocks. `` The soldiers found their lives endangered, and an officer fired one bullet which hit one of the youths. He died later,'' the spokesman said. In the incident involving the tanker driver, three Palestinians were wounded, including a 50-year-old Palestinian hit in the chest, <PERSON> Arab </PERSON> witnesses said. They said soldiers rushed to the scene, but fired only in the air to disperse the crowd. In <LOCATION> Jerusalem </LOCATION>, two people were injured slightly when the buses in which they were riding were struck with stones, police said. <LOCATION> Israel </LOCATION>'s <ORGANIZATION> Itim </ORGANIZATION> news agency reported authorities shut down the <LOCATION> Rashidiyeh </LOCATION> high school in Arab east <LOCATION> Jerusalem </LOCATION> until Oct. 31 because of a demonstration Tuesday by students protesting the suspensions of 58 classmates. It said the the 58 were suspended because they repeatedly skipped classes.
