 The <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Options </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> says it is investigating a sharp rise in trading of <ORGANIZATION> RJR </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nabisco </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> stock options in the two days prior to the company's announcement that management was considering making a $ 17 billion offer to take the company private. <ORGANIZATION> CBOE </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Warren </PERSON> <PERSON> Moulds </PERSON> said Monday that the average daily trading volume in <ORGANIZATION> RJR </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nabisco </ORGANIZATION> options in September was 1,039 contracts. Last Tuesday, 4,079 contracts were traded, he said; on Wednesday, the day preceding the announcement, 7,050 contracts were traded.
