<TEXT>
 Two of the best known names in household appliances, <ORGANIZATION> Maytag </ORGANIZATION> and <PERSON> Hoover </PERSON>, will soon be under one roof following the $ 1 billion merger of <ORGANIZATION> Maytag </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> and <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Pacific </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>. <ORGANIZATION> Maytag </ORGANIZATION> announced Monday it plans to use the European connections of <LOCATION> Hoover </LOCATION> to power its own sales overseas Investors initially drove <ORGANIZATION> Maytag </ORGANIZATION>'s value down at the news of the deal, but several analysts praised the combination as a long-term plus for the company.
</TEXT>
