<HEAD>Options Exchange Probes RJR Nabisco Trades</HEAD>
<HEAD>With PM-RJR Nabisco Bjt</HEAD>
<DATELINE>CHICAGO (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 A surge in trading of <ORGANIZATION> RJR </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nabisco </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> stock options during the two days before the announcement of a $ 17 billion management buyout plan has prompted an investigation by the <ORGANIZATION> Chicago </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Board </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Options </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>. The probe was launched last week after <ORGANIZATION> CBOE </ORGANIZATION> officials noticed a sharp rise in the number of <ORGANIZATION> RJR </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nabisco </ORGANIZATION> stock options traded last Tuesday and Wednesday, <ORGANIZATION> CBOE </ORGANIZATION> spokesman <PERSON> Warren </PERSON> <PERSON> Moulds </PERSON> said Monday. <PERSON> Moulds </PERSON> said exchange officials monitor trading through computerized systems, `` and when it breaks usual trading patterns, that usually sets in motion an inquiry into the reasons why.'' A stock option contract is a right to buy or sell 100 shares of a certain stock at a specified price within a given time period. The value of <ORGANIZATION> RJR </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nabisco </ORGANIZATION> stock options increased during the two days prior to the company's announcement. In September, only 1,039 contracts of <ORGANIZATION> RJR </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nabisco </ORGANIZATION> options were traded daily, <PERSON> Moulds </PERSON> said. Last Tuesday, 4,079 contracts were traded; on Wednesday, the day preceding the announcement, 7,050 contracts were traded. After the buyout proposal was made public on Thursday, 25,850 <ORGANIZATION> RJR </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nabisco </ORGANIZATION> options traded on the <ORGANIZATION> CBOE </ORGANIZATION>, <PERSON> Moulds </PERSON> said. After such an announcement, a large increase in trading volume is normal because the buyout plans often include a large payout to shareholders that can boost the value of the company's stock. But increased trading volume prior to the announcement can indicate that someone with advance knowledge of the company's plans was attempting to profit illegally. In a new development Monday, the investment firm <ORGANIZATION> Kohlberg </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Kravis </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Roberts </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION><ORGANIZATION> ; </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> said it would begin a $ 20.28 billion tender offer for <ORGANIZATION> RJR </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Nabisco </ORGANIZATION>. The latest <ORGANIZATION> CBOE </ORGANIZATION> inquiry follows a <ORGANIZATION> Securities </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> and </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Commission </ORGANIZATION> investigation into options trading shortly before <ORGANIZATION> Grand </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Metropolitan </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> PLC </ORGANIZATION> announced a $ 5.2 billion dollar bid for <ORGANIZATION> Pillsbury </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Co. </ORGANIZATION> earlier this month.
