<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Xerox </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION>'s third-quarter earnings rose 9 percent to $ 146 million, with a strong showing from the company's financial services division, the company said Tuesday Net income for the quarter ended Sept. 30 was up from $ 134 million in the comparable period last year. Per-share earnings were up 12 percent to $ 1.37 from $ 1.23. Revenues in the third quarter rose 10 percent to $ 4.1 billion from $ 3.8 billion last year, <ORGANIZATION> Xerox </ORGANIZATION> reported. `` Financial services continued to contribute to our earnings growth, and business products and systems again reflected the strong momentum shown in international operations all year,'' said <ORGANIZATION> Xerox </ORGANIZATION> Chairman <PERSON> David </PERSON> <PERSON> T. </PERSON> <PERSON> Kearns </PERSON>. Net income for the first nine months of 1988 was $ 465 million, an increase of 10 percent from $ 423 million in 1987. Earnings per share were $ 4.33, an 11 percent increase from $ 3.92 in the previous year. Nine-month revenues were $ 12 billion, up 10 percent from $ 11 billion last year. <ORGANIZATION> Xerox </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Financial </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> contributed $ 78 million in third-quarter net income, after allocated interest costs, a 13 percent gain from $ 69 million a year ago. In the nine-month period, financial services contributed $ 246 million to <ORGANIZATION> Xerox </ORGANIZATION> income, also up 13 percent from $ 218 million in the previous year's period. `` Our year-to-date earnings growth reflects gains in <PERSON> Crum </PERSON> and <ORGANIZATION> Forster </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION>'s property and casualty and life insurance operations, excellent growth at <ORGANIZATION> Xerox </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Credit </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> and good performance in our investment banking activities,'' said <PERSON> Melvin </PERSON> <PERSON> Howard </PERSON>, chairman of <ORGANIZATION> Xerox </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Financial </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Services </ORGANIZATION>. Business products and systems contributed $ 68 million in third-quarter earnings, up 5 percent from $ 65 million in the year-ago period. Nine-month income was $ 219 million, up 7 percent from $ 205 million a year ago. <ORGANIZATION> Xerox </ORGANIZATION> President <PERSON> Paul </PERSON> <PERSON> A. </PERSON> <PERSON> Allaire </PERSON> said the company continues to experience good growth in copier-duplicator and printing products, particularly in international operations. He said the new <ORGANIZATION> Xerox </ORGANIZATION> 50 Series copiers and duplicators are being well received and will become available worldwide by the first quarter of 1989, contributing significantly to 1989 earnings.
