<HEAD>Borden Third-Quarter Earnings Up 16.4 Percent</HEAD>
<DATELINE>NEW YORK (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Borden </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> said Tuesday its third-quarter earnings rose 16.4 percent as its sales picked up 11.6 percent from the same period a year earlier. The food, consumer products and chemical company said it earned $ 91.9 million, or $ 1.24 a share, during the quarter ended Sept. 30, up from $ 79 million, or $ 1.07 a share, in third-quarter 1987. Sales for the latest period totaled $ 1.87 billion, up from $ 1.68 billion. <PERSON> Borden </PERSON> said disappointing results in its dairy division were more than offset by gains in the company's grocery, snacks and chemicals units. For the first nine months of the year, <ORGANIZATION> Borden </ORGANIZATION> reported earnings of $ 218 million, or $ 2.95 per share, up 17.1 percent from $ 185.7 million, or $ 2.52 a share, a year earlier. Sales for the first three quarters rose to $ 5.26 billion from $ 4.71 billion.
