company announced plans to buy back shares with a current market value of more than $ 900 million. Analysts said the news gave a boost to other technology issues. As measured by <ORGANIZATION> Wilshire </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Associates </ORGANIZATION>' index of more than 5,000 actively traded stocks, the market lost $ 190 million. The <ORGANIZATION> NYSE </ORGANIZATION> index was at up .02 at 158.87. <ORGANIZATION> Standard </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; Poor's industrial index gained .18 to 325.66, and <ORGANIZATION> S </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> & </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> amp </ORGANIZATION>; P's 500-stock composite index was up .10 to 282.38. At the <ORGANIZATION> American </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION>, the market value index stood at 304.38, down .57. The NASDAQ composite index for the over-the-counter market closed at 386.12, down 1.11.
