<DATELINE>CAMBRIDGE, Mass. (AP) </DATELINE>
<TEXT>
 <ORGANIZATION> Polaroid </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Corp. </ORGANIZATION> on Tuesday posted a $ 50.4 million loss for its third quarter, due to costs of a corporate restructuring and expenses of thwarting a hostile takeover bid. <ORGANIZATION> Polaroid </ORGANIZATION> said the after-tax loss came on sales of $ 436.3 million, compared with a profit of $ 24.4 million, or 39 cents a share, on sales of $ 425.9 million in the same period of 1987. <ORGANIZATION> Polaroid </ORGANIZATION> said the loss includes a $ 97 million charge to cover costs associated with the restructuring, which included elimination of 1,300 workers under a voluntary severance plan, planned global distribution of 35mm color film and a $ 300 million employee stock ownership plan. <ORGANIZATION> Polaroid </ORGANIZATION>, which faces a hostile buyout bid from <ORGANIZATION> Disney </ORGANIZATION> family-owned <ORGANIZATION> Shamrock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Holdings </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Inc. </ORGANIZATION> of <LOCATION> Burbank </LOCATION>, <LOCATION> Calif. </LOCATION>, also attributed the decline for the quarter ending Oct. 2 to start-up costs for its new Impulse camera line. Polaroid spokesman <PERSON> Sam </PERSON> <PERSON> Yanes </PERSON> said the company spent more than $ 5 million on legal fees in the Shamrock battle and the bulk of the losses were due to the severance payments. `` Our third quarter net results reflect a variety of temporary factors that we expect to be behind us after the fourth quarter,'' Polaroid President <PERSON> I. </PERSON> <PERSON> MacAllister </PERSON> <PERSON> Booth </PERSON> said in a statement. But the company also said it expects to charge another $ 50 million in the fourth quarter to cover remaining costs of the restructuring, announced in July. For the first nine months of the year, <ORGANIZATION> Polaroid </ORGANIZATION> reported a net loss of $ 15.1 million on sales of $ 1.33 billion, compared with earnings of $ 76.3 million, or $ 1.23 a share, on sales of $ 1.25 billion in the year-earlier period. Booth predicted total savings from the restructuring of more than $ 100 million next year. He also said strong introductory sales of Impulse in <LOCATION> Europe </LOCATION> boosted international sales by 11 percent. `` The underlying soundness of our business, together with the progress we have been making in implementing our comprehensive strategic plan, give us confidence in our ability to dramatically improve the company's profitability in 1989,'' he said. <PERSON> Shamrock </PERSON> last month made a hostile $ 42-a-share offer after <ORGANIZATION> Polaroid </ORGANIZATION> rebuffed two unsolicited bids. The two companies are battling in a <LOCATION> Delaware </LOCATION> court over the legality of the 10 million share employee stock plan, which <PERSON> Shamrock </PERSON> claims was enacted to block a takeover. Two Polaroid officials took the stand in the trial in <LOCATION> Delaware </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Chancery </LOCATION> <LOCATION> Court </LOCATION> on Tuesday before Vice Chancellor <PERSON> Carolyn </PERSON> <PERSON> Berger </PERSON> delayed further hearings until Nov. 3. <ORGANIZATION> Polaroid </ORGANIZATION> stock closed at $ 37.50, down 50 cents in consolidated <ORGANIZATION> New </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> York </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Stock </ORGANIZATION> <ORGANIZATION> Exchange </ORGANIZATION> trading.
